Package: forestvalues
Title: Comprehensive Forest Economics Toolkit
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ryan", "Smith", , "rsmith@sevenislands.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for forest economic analysis including
    net present value (NPV), internal rate of return (IRR), land expectation
    value (LEV/Faustmann), optimal rotation age, stumpage valuation, income
    projection, Monte Carlo simulation, and sensitivity analysis. Designed for
    both practitioners and researchers in forest economics and natural resource
    management. All methods are documented with academic citations.
License: not for commercial or non-academic uses.
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.2
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    quarto
Config/testthat/edition: 3
